Container-based workflow for running benchmarks on a GPU cluster.

build-container
    Build the Singularity SIF image. Run on a node with the target GPU arch.

        srun -p grace --time=00:30:00 script/build-container

    Optional env vars:
        SIF        - output path (default: ~/.singularity/bigmul.sif)
        CUDA_ARCH  - nvcc arch flag (default: sm_89)

run-sbatch
    SLURM job script. Runs the benchmark binary under nsys and ncu,
    saves profiles to results/<job_id>/.

    Expects the SIF image at ~/.singularity/bigmul.sif.

submit
    Submit from a local machine through an SSH proxy.

    Required env vars:
        PROXY_HOST  - SSH proxy/bastion hostname
        REMOTE_DIR  - path to the project on the cluster

    Optional:
        CLUSTER_HOST - if the cluster login node differs from the proxy
        MAX_N        - max limb count (default: 65536)
        ITERS        - benchmark iterations (default: 3)

    Example:
        PROXY_HOST=pcad REMOTE_DIR=~/bigmul ./script/submit

test
    Verify multiply binary correctness against bc.

        make test
